Earlier, we said that for REAL data purposes, ethnicity simply means Hispanic or Latino origin.

 

Click on the button below to learn more.

Define Hispanic or Latino Origin

A person of Hispanic or Latino origin may be a person of Cuban, Mexican, Puerto Rican, South or Central American, or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race. A non-Hispanic or Latino will be a person who is not of Hispanic or Latino culture or origin.
